## Detection Rules

### Splunk — Beaconing Alert
```Splunk
index=network sourcetype=zeek_conn
| bucket _time span=1m
| stats count by id.orig_h, id.resp_h, _time
| stats stdev(count) as std avg(count) as avg 
        count as periods
  by id.orig_h, id.resp_h
| where periods > 20 AND std < 1.0
| eval alert="BEACONING DETECTED — possible C2"

```
### Splunk — DNS Tunneling Alert
```Splunk
index=network sourcetype=zeek_dns
| eval subdomain_len = len(replace(query,
    "\\.[^.]+\\.[^.]+$",""))
| where subdomain_len > 35
| stats count by query, id.orig_h
| where count > 20
| eval alert="DNS Tunneling suspected"
```
---

## Recommendations

1. Deploy Zeek on all network segments for metadata collection
2. Implement beaconing detection using statistical analysis (not just signatures)
3. Block Tor exit node IP ranges at the perimeter firewall
4. Alert on DNS queries with subdomains longer than 35 characters
5. Restrict outbound connections to approved destinations via proxy
6. Monitor `C:\Users\Public\` and `C:\Temp\` for DLL files
